pullRequest.body:
A portion of results in `Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FiniteDimensional.lean` were generalized to rings and moved to `Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FreeModule/Finite/Rank.lean`. Most API lemmas for `FiniteDimensional` are kept but replaced with one lemma proofs. Definitions and niche lemmas are replaced by the generalized version completely.

This looks like a great generalization, thanks a lot!!

Can you summarize the modification you did? Currently it is a little hard to follow everything (but it's clearly good).

Since you are at it, can you remove or at least fix the line "The definition is marked as protected to avoid conflicts with _root_.rank" in `Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Dimension`? We now have `[LinearMap.rank](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension.html#LinearMap.rank)` so I think there is no need to protect this one (or maybe there is, but the doc is still imprecise at the moment).
There are some minor issues but mostly LGTM!

```suggestion
theorem rank_span_le_of_finite {s : Set V} (hs : s.Finite) : Module.rank R (span R s) ≤ #s := by
```
Maybe you can add `Module.Free R V` to a `variable` line.
Is there a reason why this results are here? Since they don't concern free modules.

I think I'll reorganize `LinearAlgebra/Dimension.lean`, `LinearAlgebra/Finrank.lean`, `LinearAlgebra/FreeModule/Finite/Rank.lean`, `LinearAlgebra/FreeModule/Rank.lean` (and maybe `LinearAlgebra.FiniteDimensional`?) into a new folder under `LinearAlgebra` after I generalized all the results, as there are already lots of misplaced lemmas and some files mentioned above also needs to be splitted.
OK, no problem for doing it in another PR (anyway it is already a mess...). Can you just add a TODO?

already in `variable`.



```suggestion
theorem Module.finite_of_finrank_pos (h : finrank R V ≠ 0) :
```
could be more convenient, and it's just a rewrite (by [not_imp_comm](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#not_imp_comm)) from the previous lemma.
I'm not planning to change the lemma statements in this PR.

Cardinal is already opened, right?
```suggestion
  simp only [← rank_lt_alpeh0_iff, hVW, nsmul_lt_aleph0_iff_of_ne_zero hn]
```

```suggestion
noncomputable def Basis.unique {ι : Type*} (b : Basis ι R R) : Unique ι := by
```
You moved this and the following lemmas from FiniteDimensional.lean. Why not use `namespace FiniteDimensional` as it was the case?
I'll have to rename them anyway. This has nothing to do with `FiniteDimensional`

I just don't understand why you manually added the "wrong" namespace to each declaration. If you put them in a `namespace FiniteDimensional` section, wouldn't it be easier to change it to `namespace Module.Finite` in the future?
I agree with this comment. Is the namespace to keep the actual name? In this case we can add a TODO (but using `namespace` seems anyway a good idea).

```suggestion
    (v : ι → V) : ¬LinearIndependent K v :=
  fun h_lin_indep ↦ (lt_aleph0_of_linearIndependent h_lin_indep).not_le (infinite_iff.mp inf)
```
(untested)

and you've already [generalized](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/8912/files#diff-6b9b42075c59a19ba76df0a68785e5574b46de22a1a0dcc55ccbbf7304838dccR371-R377) this to Module.Finite.
Side comment: this and the next lemmas are good golfing targets ...
Add a TODO?
Can you just put these into RingTheory.Finiteness? They don't require StrongRankCondition at all.
A lot of lemmas in this file are already misplaced and will need a cleanup PR later. I can move these lemmas first if you insist.

As [mathlib docs shows]([Submodule.fg_iff_finite](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FreeModule/Finite/Rank.html#Submodule.fg_iff_finite)) these already don't use StrongRankCondition. I'm removing the condition from `variable` in #9152 so that it won't be forgotten. I refrain from moving the lemmas, awaiting the misplacement cleanup PR.
Should this be `coe_finrank_eq_card_basis`? I guess we could also omit the `coe` ... `Cardinal.mk` doesn't appear in the LHS.
